California, with senior water rights, would face cuts last in the Colorado River crisis.
Rising temperatures in the West have led to increased drought severity.
The seven Colorado basin states are battling for dwindling river flows.
Urban areas may soon take precedence over agriculture for water allocation.
The ongoing drought has left reservoirs half empty, prompting discussions on water conservation.
The Colorado River faces a future of reduced flows, impacting millions who rely on it.
Efforts are being made to address water shortages and potential conflicts among states sharing the river's resources.
